notes:
API reference from docs/mrt2-integration.md ("Recording Buffer" section):
runner->start_recording();
runner->stop_recording();
size_t count = runner->get_recorded_sample_count();
runner->get_recorded_audio(dest_L, dest_R, start_idx, count);
runner->get_waveform_peaks(200); // bucketed peak amplitudes for a UI thumbnail, not needed for WAV export

Engine maintains an internal circular recording buffer of ALL generated audio automatically -- no manual sample-capture loop needed on our side. We just call start_recording()/stop_recording() around the desired window and pull via get_recorded_audio() into a WAV writer.
